				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\rm{El}} = \frac{{\Delta T}}{{\Delta {\rm{St}}}},$$\end{document}El=ΔTΔSt,where T is the fabric tension per unit length in gf/cm and St is the fabric extension. Assuming that we have a tubular fabric covering a cylindrical tube, the fabric extension and the size of the reduction (Re) are given by2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
