				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\rm{St}} = \frac{{{\rm{Re}}}}{{1 - {\rm{Re}}}},$$\end{document}St=Re1−Re,where R is the radius of a cylindrical tube and r is the radius of tubular elastic fabric (R > r). By applying Laplace’s law, the pressure (P) in gf/cm2 can be defined as5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
